<topic id="to_respond_to_rfq_0">
   <title>To respond to RFQ</title>
   <prolog>
      <author>Metapercept</author>
      <critdates>
         <created date="2025-11-21+05:30"/>
         <revised modified="2025-05-05"/>
      </critdates>
      <metadata>
         <audience type="role"
                   platform="web"
                   product="metR-Power-Source_To_Pay_User_Guide_Final"/>
         <keywords>
            <keyword/>
            <indexterm/>
            <indexterm/>
         </keywords>
         <othermeta name="title" content=""/>
         <othermeta name="shortdesc" content=""/>
      </metadata>
      <resourceid appid="" appname="" id="" ux-source-priority="topic-and-map"/>
   </prolog>
   <body>
      <context/>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>Click the<uicontrol>Sourcing Events</uicontrol> tab.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Select the appropriate sourcing event and click View.</p>
            <p>
               <fig id="fig_bch_bcg_12c">
                  <image placement="break"
                         width="700"
                         href="../attachments/69206020/69206098.png"
                         id="image_cch_bcg_12c"/>
               </fig>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Click the <uicontrol>RFQ</uicontrol> tab.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Click View RFQ. </p>
            <p>
               <fig id="fig_uc3_2cg_12c">
                  <image placement="break"
                         width="700"
                         href="../attachments/69206020/69206100.png"
                         id="image_vc3_2cg_12c"/>
               </fig>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>To download the RFQ, click Download.</p>
            <p>
               <fig id="fig_x14_fcg_12c">
                  <image placement="break"
                         width="700"
                         href="../attachments/69206020/69206121.png"
                         id="image_y14_fcg_12c"/>
               </fig>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>To respond to the RFQ, click Create Response.</p>
            <p>
               <fig id="fig_vtp_gcg_12c">
                  <image placement="break"
                         width="700"
                         href="../attachments/69206020/69206127.png"
                         id="image_wtp_gcg_12c"/>
               </fig>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Enter the appropriate responses.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Select the Group Name check box and click Refresh to view the
                        Total.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Select the price modifiers that are applicable. You can add comments in the
                        Comment text box. </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>To upload an attachment, click Upload.</p>
            <p>
               <fig id="fig_bwj_kcg_12c">
                  <image placement="break"
                         width="700"
                         href="../attachments/69206020/69206163.png"
                         id="image_cwj_kcg_12c"/>
               </fig>
               <note type="note" id="note_jlz_kcg_12c">
                  <p>For the Attachments in Apttus STP, you can upload any file. We
                            allow files of the following extension types: (.PDF), (.RTF), (.RTX),
                            (.TXT), (.JPG), (.JPEG), (.PNG), (.GIF), (.TIF), (.BMP), (.DOC),
                            (.DOCX), (.DOCM), (.PPT), (.PPTX), (.PPTM), (.PPS), (.PPSX), (.XLS),
                            (.XLSX), (.XLSM), (.ZIP), (.MP3), (.M4A), (.OGG), (.WAV), (.MP4),
                            (.M4V), (.MOV), (.OGV), (.3GP), (.3G2). The application might become
                            slow if you upload a file higher than 25 MB.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Click <uicontrol>Choose File</uicontrol> and select the appropriate file.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Enter the FileDescription.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Select the appropriate permission from the Permissions picklist menu.</p>
            <p>
               <table id="table_hq3_ncg_12c">
                  <tgroup cols="2">
                     <thead>
                        <row>
                           <entry>
                              <p>Permission</p>
                           </entry>
                           <entry>
                              <p>Description</p>
                           </entry>
                        </row>
                     </thead>
                     <tbody>
                        <row>
                           <entry>
                              <p>Public</p>
                           </entry>
                           <entry>
                              <p>To make the attachment available to all the
                                            Suppliers.</p>
                           </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                           <entry>
                              <p>Private</p>
                           </entry>
                           <entry>
                              <p>To make the attachment available to only the Buyer.</p>
                           </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                           <entry>
                              <p>Selective Public</p>
                           </entry>
                           <entry>
                              <p>To make the attachment available to the selected
                                            Supplier(s).</p>
                              <p>Note: At least one supplier must be selected for
                                            this option.</p>
                           </entry>
                        </row>
                     </tbody>
                  </tgroup>
               </table>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Click <uicontrol>Attach.</uicontrol>
            </p>
            <p>
               <fig id="fig_x4v_4cg_12c">
                  <image placement="break"
                         width="700"
                         href="../attachments/69206020/69206056.png"
                         id="image_y4v_4cg_12c"/>
               </fig>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Click Save.</p>
            <p>
               <fig id="fig_uwl_qcg_12c">
                  <image placement="break"
                         width="700"
                         href="../attachments/69206020/69206142.png"
                         id="image_vwl_qcg_12c"/>
               </fig>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>To edit an attachment, click Edit.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>To delete an attachment, click Delete.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Click <uicontrol>Submit Response</uicontrol>. </p>
            <p>
               <fig id="fig_u4r_scg_12c">
                  <image placement="break"
                         width="700"
                         href="../attachments/69206020/69206133.png"
                         id="image_v4r_scg_12c"/>
               </fig>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Click the <uicontrol>Back to Sourcing Event link</uicontrol> .</p>
            <p>
               <note type="note" id="note_yjs_tcg_12c">
                  <p>Once you submit your response to the buyer, View RFQ and View
                                Response links are visible on the Sourcing Event Detail page.
                            You can edit the responses before the RFQ deadline. Ensure that you
                            click Submit Response after you have edited the response.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
         </li>
      </ol>
   </body>
</topic>
